Kvass.

00:58.405 --> 01:01.606
Best I ever made.

01:01.641 --> 01:02.607
[ Glasses clank ]

01:02.642 --> 01:04.075
- [ Chuckles ]
- Mm.

01:07.080 --> 01:09.247
Mm.
I like it.

01:09.282 --> 01:11.249
Mm? Yeah?

01:11.284 --> 01:13.650
Yeah.

01:13.686 --> 01:17.388
Nice here
when nobody home.

01:17.423 --> 01:21.458
Peaceful.
No fights...

01:21.494 --> 01:22.526
[ Chuckles ]

01:22.561 --> 01:23.960
You fight with Dee?

01:23.996 --> 01:25.829
[ Chuckles ]
She's my wife,

01:25.865 --> 01:27.998
I'm gonna fight with her,
right?

01:28.033 --> 01:29.966
Although, it's been
pretty good lately.

01:30.002 --> 01:32.603
I mean, helps that we
never see each other...

01:32.638 --> 01:35.472
[ Scoffs ]
What about Tuan?

01:35.508 --> 01:37.841
You... have nice relationship
with him?

01:37.877 --> 01:40.510
Mm. Sure.

01:40.545 --> 01:44.381
I mean, I-I know he looks
pretty even-tempered,

01:44.416 --> 01:47.384
but, um,
Tuan can be a handful.

01:49.754 --> 01:51.988
Me and Pasha, you know,
we fight all the time.

01:52.024 --> 01:53.723
- You see this, right?
- Mm.

01:53.758 --> 01:56.225
But now?
No fights.

01:58.630 --> 01:59.862
He just quiet.

01:59.898 --> 02:04.500
He like dog,
somebody beat with stick.

02:06.638 --> 02:09.472
Just sad. Sad.
Very sad boy.

02:09.507 --> 02:12.874
[ Inhales deeply,
lips smack ]

02:12.910 --> 02:16.812
Promise not to say to Evgheniya
what I tell you now-- okay?

02:16.847 --> 02:19.214
Of course.

02:19.250 --> 02:20.816
[ Lips smack ]

02:24.021 --> 02:27.556
I miss kvass.

02:27.591 --> 02:28.857
Talk with friends.

02:28.892 --> 02:30.725
The street I live in.

02:30.761 --> 02:33.728
This place-- it--
have food,

02:33.764 --> 02:39.367
have money--
but not so easy to be happy.

02:40.604 --> 02:42.704
Have I tell you
about my mother?

02:45.275 --> 02:48.109
She was teacher of biology
at university.

02:48.144 --> 02:50.578
And I go to her
after her classes,

02:50.613 --> 02:54.015
and we are going home,
and she must prepare dinner

02:54.050 --> 02:56.084
after long day of work--
but she says,

02:56.119 --> 02:59.854
"No,
we go skating first."

02:59.889 --> 03:03.891
And just like this,
we go ice skating.

03:03.926 --> 03:06.426
And we skate and skate
and skate,

03:06.462 --> 03:08.328
night comes,
we still skate.

03:08.364 --> 03:11.164
Just never want to stop.
[ Sighs ]

03:11.200 --> 03:15.603
My father was gone then.
But...

03:15.638 --> 03:17.605
[ Sighs ]

03:20.409 --> 03:21.908
Mama...

03:24.913 --> 03:27.981
Moscow was nice city
with my mother.

03:41.863 --> 03:44.263
[ Door opens ]

03:47.869 --> 03:50.102
[ Door creaking ]

04:10.424 --> 04:13.425
I know I made a mistake.

04:13.460 --> 04:17.495
I'm... I'm sorry.

04:17.531 --> 04:20.331
I f-- I failed you.
I failed my people.

04:20.367 --> 04:22.467
Everything
you've been through,

04:22.502 --> 04:25.770
your family,
your country...

04:25.805 --> 04:29.074
you're special, Tuan.

04:29.109 --> 04:31.309
I admire you.

04:31.344 --> 04:33.678
I believe in you.

04:33.713 --> 04:35.613
You're fighting
so things like that

04:35.648 --> 04:37.648
won't happen
to other people.

04:39.553 --> 04:43.253
I wish I could tell you
it gets easier.

04:43.289 --> 04:46.190
It doesn't.

04:46.225 --> 04:49.293
But you can do this.

04:49.328 --> 04:51.328
You can be great at it.

04:54.366 --> 04:57.301
Thank you.

04:57.336 --> 04:59.069
But don't make a mistake
like that again.

04:59.105 --> 05:01.738
It's not worth it.

05:01.773 --> 05:04.007
Did you report me?

05:04.042 --> 05:05.476
No.

05:05.511 --> 05:06.810
You hungry?

05:06.845 --> 05:08.945
[ Door creaking ]

05:12.684 --> 05:13.750
How'd it go?

05:13.785 --> 05:15.085
Uh.
[ Sighs ]

05:15.120 --> 05:18.354
Sounds like Pasha's
doing worse.

05:18.389 --> 05:20.624
He tell you about
the shit in his locker?

05:20.659 --> 05:23.693
- [ Keys clatter ]
- Human shit?

05:23.729 --> 05:26.195
No.

05:26.231 --> 05:30.866
I got this asshole Darren Burke
to get some from his dog,

05:30.901 --> 05:33.569
put it in a bag,
then him and his friends

05:33.605 --> 05:37.006
dump it out
in Pasha's locker.

05:37.041 --> 05:39.708
They thought it was
the funniest thing in the world.

05:39.744 --> 05:43.212
Pasha has no idea
I got them to do it.

05:43.248 --> 05:46.882
I'm not sure that they know
I got them to do it.

05:46.917 --> 05:48.283
Good.

05:51.122 --> 05:53.122
[ Insects chirping ]

05:55.559 --> 05:59.394
[ Door opens, closes ]

06:02.533 --> 06:06.234
- Honey?
- Hi.

06:06.270 --> 06:07.569
What are you doing?

06:07.604 --> 06:09.103
Cleaning.

06:12.008 --> 06:13.841
It's a little late.

06:15.745 --> 06:17.979
Hey.

06:18.014 --> 06:19.481
What's going on?

06:19.516 --> 06:21.683
Hey, hey.

06:21.718 --> 06:23.685
Did you babysit tonight?

06:23.720 --> 06:25.219
- Yeah.
- Did something happen?

06:31.327 --> 06:36.697
Pastor Tim thinks
I might really be screwed up.

06:36.732 --> 06:39.366
He's worried
about my soul.

06:39.402 --> 06:41.435
He said that?

06:41.470 --> 06:43.937
No.
I-I read his diary again.

06:43.972 --> 06:45.639
- [ Sighs ]
- I know I shouldn't have,

06:45.675 --> 06:47.608
you don't have
to say that.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.445
Paige,
he doesn't know anything.

06:51.480 --> 06:53.714
You can't listen
to him.

06:53.749 --> 06:56.216
He cares about me.
You said that yourself.

06:56.251 --> 06:59.186
He doesn't
really know you.

06:59.221 --> 07:00.754
I don't know.

07:00.789 --> 07:04.457
I think...

07:04.492 --> 07:07.594
maybe I am screwed up.

07:07.629 --> 07:10.463
Because of...

07:10.498 --> 07:13.866
Pastor Tim thinks
it's because of all the lying...

07:13.901 --> 07:15.535
Everyone thinks
they're screwed up.

07:15.570 --> 07:17.604
That's what I've learned.

07:17.639 --> 07:19.439
It wasn't exactly lying,
Paige.

07:19.474 --> 07:21.874
We kept things from you.
We had to.

07:21.909 --> 07:23.876
To protect you
and our family.

07:23.911 --> 07:26.445
And when you were ready
we told you.

07:26.480 --> 07:28.748
[ Insects chirping ]

07:31.518 --> 07:34.486
♪♪

07:54.530 --> 07:56.196
