[ Rhythmic knock on door ]

12:17.679 --> 12:18.912
Hey. Come in.

12:18.947 --> 12:22.415
Hello.

12:22.450 --> 12:24.584
- [ Door closes ]
- Was there any problem?

12:24.620 --> 12:26.620
No. It was easy.

12:26.655 --> 12:29.555
I took the elevator
from my apartment.

12:29.591 --> 12:34.127
And nobody in elevator.
Nobody in hallway.

12:34.162 --> 12:40.733
So you rent this place
in my building just to see me?

12:40.768 --> 12:42.535
Is so expensive.

12:42.570 --> 12:44.903
Well, we told you we'd do
what we had to to keep you safe.

12:44.939 --> 12:47.940
- [ Chuckles ]
- So, how's it going with the dentist?

12:49.343 --> 12:50.876
[ Clicks tongue ]
Wow.

12:50.911 --> 12:53.712
I was there four times.
Good.

12:53.748 --> 12:55.814
[ Inhales deeply ]
Thank you.

12:55.850 --> 12:57.683
- Sure.
- No, I really thank you.

12:57.718 --> 12:59.151
The pain
is almost gone.

12:59.186 --> 13:00.585
Oh, good.

13:00.621 --> 13:03.555
There is a man...

13:03.590 --> 13:05.390
Um.

13:05.425 --> 13:09.027
We're getting closer,

13:09.062 --> 13:13.298
and--
is getting better.

13:13.333 --> 13:15.534
Well, that's great.
Good for you.

13:15.569 --> 13:17.636
So,
who's the lucky guy?

13:17.671 --> 13:21.173
He is a very famous man
in Soviet Union.

13:21.208 --> 13:25.910
Gennadi Bystrov.
He was a defenseman.

13:25.945 --> 13:28.880
Of Soviet national team.

13:28.915 --> 13:31.415
- They are champions--
- Sure. Yeah, I know.

13:31.450 --> 13:33.484
- The Soviet national team.
- We know.

13:33.519 --> 13:36.420
He is really nice
and friendly.

13:36.455 --> 13:39.223
Last time, when he came
to United States,

13:39.258 --> 13:45.596
uh, he, uh,
brought the gift for my boy.

13:45.631 --> 13:49.533
Hockey... shirt.

13:49.569 --> 13:51.602
My boy loves it.

13:51.637 --> 13:53.804
Oh, he visits you here?
Bystrov?

13:53.839 --> 13:56.973
Yes, he carries package over.
For government.

13:57.009 --> 13:59.776
Oh, well, that's great.
So you get to see him a lot.

14:02.181 --> 14:04.981
Sounds like he gets along well
with your son...

14:05.017 --> 14:07.517
My son loves him.

14:07.552 --> 14:12.255
He is very good man,
Gennadi.

14:21.833 --> 14:24.066
Anything good?

14:24.102 --> 14:26.869
Something happened
in Ghazni.

14:26.904 --> 14:32.307
Mujahedeen were killed by some
kind of hemorrhagic fever.

14:32.343 --> 14:37.880
We sent a sample of
the Lassa virus to the Centre.

14:37.915 --> 14:41.917
That's
a hemorrhagic fever.

14:41.953 --> 14:45.254
We were told it was being
developed for defense.

14:45.289 --> 14:46.955
In case Reagan...

14:46.990 --> 14:50.325
I don't know
anything about it.

14:50.361 --> 14:52.026
I'm sorry...

14:54.465 --> 14:56.565
[ Clears throat ]

14:59.303 --> 15:02.871
We've been talking
about Pastor Tim...

15:02.906 --> 15:04.873
we're wondering if you think
the Centre

15:04.908 --> 15:07.275
might be able to get him
a job offer.

15:07.310 --> 15:09.443
Somewhere far away.

15:11.148 --> 15:13.782
Anything else
I should know about it?

15:13.817 --> 15:15.316
Not really.

15:16.820 --> 15:18.118
There are peace groups,

15:18.154 --> 15:21.355
international religious
councils.

15:21.391 --> 15:23.190
Do you want me
to look into it?

15:23.225 --> 15:26.360
We'll let you know.

15:26.396 --> 15:30.298
Um, the Centre analyzed
the wheat sample you sent.

15:30.333 --> 15:32.166
They say
it's remarkable.

15:32.201 --> 15:35.269
They suspect it was bred partly
from a Kazakh variety,

15:35.304 --> 15:37.704
which is surprising.

15:37.739 --> 15:41.275
Stolen. From us.

15:41.310 --> 15:45.545
Our agronomists are gonna be
working on it for some time.

15:45.580 --> 15:47.514
Some time?

15:47.549 --> 15:50.517
Years.

15:50.552 --> 15:57.324
So you'll have to keep running
Stobert and Kemp long term.

16:12.798 --> 16:15.200
[ Birds chirping ]

16:19.240 --> 16:21.940
- [ Knock on door ]
- Come in.

16:26.679 --> 16:29.280
Hi.

16:29.315 --> 16:32.984
Um, so
your mom and I

16:33.019 --> 16:35.653
have been talking about
what happened. What you read.

16:35.688 --> 16:37.789
And we know
you're upset about it...

16:37.824 --> 16:39.957
We're upset about it.

16:39.992 --> 16:41.992
We don't think you should have
to be around him anymore.

16:42.027 --> 16:44.729
W-We don't think
you should have to manage him

16:44.764 --> 16:47.331
for the rest
of your life.

16:47.367 --> 16:50.601
We had an idea...

16:50.637 --> 16:52.637
um...

16:55.107 --> 16:57.707
we thought that maybe
we could talk to the people

16:57.743 --> 17:01.145
we work with and they might
be able to get Pastor Tim

17:01.180 --> 17:02.946
a job offer.

17:02.982 --> 17:06.049
Doing something that would
make him really happy.

17:06.085 --> 17:10.720
Maybe in Europe, maybe charity
work, something religious.

17:10.756 --> 17:12.954
Somewhere far away.

17:14.992 --> 17:17.294
Just if you wanted
to think about that.

17:17.329 --> 17:19.262
We didn't bring this up
before because we didn't think

17:19.298 --> 17:21.498
it was something
you would want, but...

17:21.532 --> 17:24.967
I don't know... that--
that seems weird.

17:25.002 --> 17:26.770
I mean, without him
even knowing...?

17:26.805 --> 17:28.605
We would only do it
if it were something

17:28.640 --> 17:30.206
that would
be good for him.

17:30.241 --> 17:33.176
And we'd never do it
if you didn't want us to.

17:46.089 --> 17:48.490
What's going on
with the people who wanted

17:48.526 --> 17:53.261
to destroy your crops
with the bugs and stuff?

17:53.297 --> 17:54.996
It's not gonna happen.

17:55.032 --> 17:56.432
You stopped it?

17:56.467 --> 17:58.567
It was complicated.

17:58.602 --> 18:01.269
But... they're not
doing it now.

18:01.305 --> 18:04.940
And we were able to get a sample
of the special kind of wheat

18:04.975 --> 18:06.774
the US has been developing.

18:06.810 --> 18:09.978
So maybe our country
can now grow better food.

18:10.013 --> 18:12.680
I mean, it wasn't just us,
but... it does feel good

18:12.716 --> 18:14.415
when you can make
a difference.

18:16.854 --> 18:23.391
You did something so huge,
and no one even knows.

18:23.426 --> 18:24.992
That's how it works.

18:29.733 --> 18:31.399
[ Sighs ]

18:36.873 --> 18:38.939
- That was good.
- Yeah.

18:40.776 --> 18:44.778
I have to go back to Topeka
on the 19th.

18:44.813 --> 18:46.713
More Tai Chi?

18:49.218 --> 18:50.985
Yeah.

19:14.075 --> 19:17.310
[ Sighs ]

19:47.808 --> 19:49.507
[ Sighs ]

19:52.112 --> 19:54.947
[ Silverware taps lightly ]

20:10.330 --> 20:13.565
They better. I think.
Some of them.

20:13.600 --> 20:17.068
They know more words now
but how they say words.

20:17.103 --> 20:18.669
The, um...

20:18.704 --> 20:20.004
The pronunciation?

20:20.039 --> 20:22.573
- Yes. It's very bad.
- Yes.

20:22.608 --> 20:24.342
It's hard to learn
new language

20:24.377 --> 20:25.676
when don't speak it
all time.

20:25.711 --> 20:27.478
That is how
Tuan caught on.

20:27.513 --> 20:28.846
No one spoke Vietnamese

20:28.881 --> 20:30.747
so he was just
forced to learn English.

20:30.783 --> 20:32.916
Maybe we need speak
only English at home.

20:32.952 --> 20:34.551
- [ Chuckles ]
- Help Pasha speak better.

20:34.587 --> 20:36.152
That's what school
is for.

20:36.188 --> 20:37.721
Tuan learned
so much faster

20:37.756 --> 20:41.157
once he got around
kids his own age.

20:41.193 --> 20:43.760
School is...

20:43.796 --> 20:45.762
School is not so good
for Pasha.

20:45.798 --> 20:48.398
I thought he was doing
so much better.

20:48.433 --> 20:50.933
No.

20:50.969 --> 20:54.637
Some kid they...

20:54.672 --> 20:58.074
they put... shit
in Pasha locker.

20:58.110 --> 20:59.342
Oh my God.

20:59.378 --> 21:01.244
I never heard
of this before.

21:01.279 --> 21:04.213
How can person do that?

21:04.248 --> 21:06.248
Now he hate school
even more.

21:06.283 --> 21:08.083
He don't want to go ever.

21:08.119 --> 21:10.553
Every day we fight
to get him out of house.

21:10.588 --> 21:14.156
I'm so sorry.
I--

21:14.191 --> 21:17.827
Tuan always sort of had
an easy time with friends.

21:17.862 --> 21:20.095
You know him,
he's... got that personality.

21:20.131 --> 21:21.530
Didn't get it
from me or Brad.

21:21.565 --> 21:23.365
He's just positive.

21:23.401 --> 21:27.403
And I think that
made things easier for him.

21:27.438 --> 21:31.140
Well,
Pasha not that way.

21:31.175 --> 21:33.575
No.

21:33.610 --> 21:35.777
But, you know,
I-I know a lot of kids

21:35.812 --> 21:38.780
who have gone through
that sort of thing.

21:38.815 --> 21:43.484
Most kids at some point.
And it does get better.

21:46.489 --> 21:49.558
What if not?

21:49.593 --> 21:53.161
What if just worse?

21:53.196 --> 21:56.230
[ Sighs ]
Oh my God. It's so bad.

21:57.900 --> 21:59.467
I know.

21:59.502 --> 22:04.105
No.
Not just Pasha.

22:04.140 --> 22:06.474
I...

22:10.279 --> 22:14.949
One of my student...
we-- we have sex.

22:14.984 --> 22:17.150
[ Inhales deeply ]

22:17.186 --> 22:18.919
Oh.

22:18.955 --> 22:22.489
I was so mad at Alexei.
We fight, fight all time.

22:22.524 --> 22:25.392
And with my student,
was so nice

22:25.427 --> 22:29.129
and easy and fun and...

22:29.164 --> 22:32.031
But now Alexei-- he try.
He try not fight.

22:32.067 --> 22:34.667
He try be nice to me.

22:34.703 --> 22:38.638
For Pasha,
he say we must be strong.

22:38.673 --> 22:40.840
I feel bad
all time now.

22:40.875 --> 22:43.776
[ Sniffles ]

22:43.812 --> 22:45.511
What do you want to do?

22:45.546 --> 22:49.115
I want make
none of this happen.

22:49.150 --> 22:51.751
I want my family
be happy.

22:51.786 --> 22:53.987
Then fight for that.

22:58.793 --> 22:59.992
[ Laughter ]

23:00.027 --> 23:01.827
I think you'd be
fantastic at it.

23:01.862 --> 23:03.996
- Well, we'll never know.
- [ Laughs ]

23:04.031 --> 23:07.199
I told him if he sang
one song. Just one.

23:07.235 --> 23:08.534
Then he could come
to my softball games.

23:08.569 --> 23:11.504
Hey. Give up.
I am never doing karaoke.

23:11.539 --> 23:13.005
I-I'm with you.

23:13.040 --> 23:15.207
There-- There's not enough
