in distance ]

23:38.965 --> 23:41.565
[ Whispers ]
Okay.

23:52.911 --> 23:54.411
[ Horn honks ]

23:56.014 --> 23:58.315
[ Sighs ]

24:03.222 --> 24:05.289
Why does this
bother you so much?

24:05.324 --> 24:07.257
It just does.

24:10.228 --> 24:14.363
The Centre has nothing
to do with them, come on.

24:14.399 --> 24:16.700
And so what if they do?

24:19.971 --> 24:23.372
I don't want Stan
to be like Martha.

24:26.444 --> 24:28.944
[ Keys jingle ]

24:28.979 --> 24:30.946
[ Engine starts ]

24:39.669 --> 24:41.569
Howard: You're in the dark.

24:41.605 --> 24:44.840
So what do you do?

24:44.875 --> 24:47.809
You hold out your hands.

24:47.845 --> 24:49.177
Makes sense.

24:49.212 --> 24:51.780
You don't want to bump
into anything.

24:51.815 --> 24:54.282
But if someone
turns on the light

24:54.317 --> 24:59.820
and there's nothing there,
do you feel stupid?

24:59.856 --> 25:01.389
You probably
look pretty stupid.

25:01.424 --> 25:04.058
[ Laughter ]

25:04.093 --> 25:08.229
If you'd felt something,
would that have made you smart?

25:08.265 --> 25:10.931
The point is when
you're walking in the dark

25:10.967 --> 25:12.533
you don't know the answer,

25:12.568 --> 25:15.836
but you have an instinct
for how to move forward.

25:15.872 --> 25:18.172
The instinct is neither
right or wrong.

25:18.207 --> 25:21.408
It just is.

25:21.443 --> 25:24.278
We're all machines.

25:24.313 --> 25:26.580
Say hello to the machine
sitting next to you.

25:26.615 --> 25:30.950
Because that's what you are.
Machines.

25:30.986 --> 25:33.853
Go ahead.
Say "hello."

25:33.889 --> 25:38.258
- Hello.
- Your lives are mechanically programmed--

25:38.294 --> 25:43.096
stimulus, response--
stimulus, response--

25:43.131 --> 25:46.900
stimulus, response.

25:46.935 --> 25:49.169
But if we're nothing more
than machines

25:49.204 --> 25:51.905
programmed to respond
to stimuli,

25:51.940 --> 25:56.009
what are we to make
of the notion of enlightenment?

25:56.044 --> 26:00.379
Enlightenment
is knowing the truth,

26:00.415 --> 26:03.716
accepting that you are
a machine.

26:11.259 --> 26:13.559
[ Door opens ]

26:13.595 --> 26:15.961
[ Birds chirping ]

26:29.810 --> 26:32.310
You should go out.
Get some air.

26:40.320 --> 26:42.454
What?

26:48.461 --> 26:50.795
[ Sighs ]

26:50.830 --> 26:55.099
Look, what he wrote about you,
Paige...

26:55.135 --> 27:00.772
you know, I-I still go to these
EST meetings sometimes...

27:00.807 --> 27:03.307
and they make you think about
the hard stuff in life...

27:03.342 --> 27:05.075
things that you've asked.

27:05.110 --> 27:09.980
Like how did we end up
doing this.

27:12.652 --> 27:17.321
One of the things they say...
is who you are as a kid...

27:17.356 --> 27:20.123
you don't have
to stay that way.

27:26.231 --> 27:32.402
Some of what he wrote...
it's like... about who I am.

27:32.437 --> 27:34.871
Who he thinks I am.

27:34.907 --> 27:36.539
It doesn't matter
what he wrote.

27:36.574 --> 27:38.708
Well, something
was true about it.

27:38.743 --> 27:39.975
- Well--
- You know that.

27:40.011 --> 27:41.544
Even if he was
to write something

27:41.579 --> 27:44.046
that's true
a little bit... so what?

27:44.081 --> 27:45.948
He doesn't know
who you are.

27:48.520 --> 27:50.820
[ Sighs ]

27:54.525 --> 28:00.629
You could change his whole life
and he'd never even know it.

28:00.664 --> 28:01.997
We can't make him
take the job.

28:02.033 --> 28:05.500
We'd just be giving him
an opportunity.

28:05.536 --> 28:07.303
That you know
he'll want.

28:07.338 --> 28:09.071
More or less.

28:16.079 --> 28:21.316
Henry knows
what he wants.

28:21.352 --> 28:23.485
He's still a kid.

28:23.520 --> 28:26.722
It's not like he wants
to get drunk and do drugs.

28:26.757 --> 28:28.990
It--
It's nothing bad.

28:29.025 --> 28:32.093
He knows there's
a better place for him.

28:32.128 --> 28:35.696
I think
he'd be better off.

28:35.732 --> 28:39.901
Henry's...

28:39.936 --> 28:42.070
He's different.

28:49.111 --> 28:52.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

28:52.615 --> 28:54.882
[ Door opens ]

28:54.917 --> 28:58.686
♪♪

29:46.366 --> 29:48.300
Running low on beans.

29:48.335 --> 29:50.268
Uh, the black ones?

29:50.304 --> 29:51.436
Red.

29:51.471 --> 29:53.071
Got it.

30:01.681 --> 30:04.982
[ Sighs softly ]

30:05.017 --> 30:09.053
I think about the people
who need this stuff,

30:09.088 --> 30:11.522
standing in line
for food...

30:11.558 --> 30:13.723
makes me feel
pretty lucky.

30:13.759 --> 30:15.926
I think you are.

30:15.962 --> 30:17.328
Look where you've come
in the last year,

30:17.363 --> 30:19.729
how much you've grown.

30:19.765 --> 30:24.335
You are definitely moving
in the right direction.

30:24.370 --> 30:26.603
I don't know.

30:26.638 --> 30:30.440
Sometimes I feel like...

30:35.881 --> 30:39.783
You have a lot to handle,
but you're handling it.

30:39.818 --> 30:44.554
Look to your faith.
Your faith will keep you strong.

30:44.590 --> 30:48.191
"Cast your cares on the Lord
and he will sustain you;

30:48.226 --> 30:52.828
he will never let
the righteous be shaken."

30:52.864 --> 30:54.597
[ Inhales deeply ]

30:54.632 --> 30:56.799
You're gonna do
great in life.

30:59.270 --> 31:04.039
There's not a doubt
in my mind about that.

31:04.074 --> 31:07.275
[ Cans clatter ]

31:10.048 --> 31:13.118
They transport the documents
on undeveloped film.

31:13.153 --> 31:14.586
Spooled up around cotton,

31:14.621 --> 31:17.054
with a prophylactic
in the middle--

31:17.090 --> 31:18.789
a condom filled with ammonia.

31:18.825 --> 31:20.625
Now, the courier doesn't know
how to defeat the trap.

31:20.660 --> 31:24.261
The only person who does is
one officer at the Rezidentura.

31:24.296 --> 31:25.997
But they transport
a lot of other things

31:26.032 --> 31:27.397
in the diplomatic pouch, too.

31:27.433 --> 31:29.233
Guns, electronic devices,

31:29.268 --> 31:30.801
circuit boards,
other technology.

31:30.837 --> 31:32.103
Things that they've stolen

31:32.138 --> 31:34.171
and that they're
sending back home.

31:34.206 --> 31:36.406
The outer pouch
is tamper-proof--

31:36.442 --> 31:37.908
all one-time locks and seals.

31:37.944 --> 31:39.777
We've never gotten past them.

31:39.812 --> 31:41.778
But since our last attempt
three years ago,

31:41.813 --> 31:45.182
we've been working
on a new approach.

31:45.217 --> 31:48.252
Now, Bystrov comes in
approximately twice a month.

31:48.287 --> 31:51.421
Always on diplomatic
Aeroflot flights to JFK.

31:51.457 --> 31:53.157
The couriers work in pairs,

31:53.192 --> 31:55.592
and one of them
always stays with the pouch.

31:55.628 --> 31:57.226
Now, when one of them
has to use the bathroom

31:57.262 --> 32:00.496
at the airport,
they both go in.

32:00.532 --> 32:02.331
One stays outside the stall,

32:02.367 --> 32:05.935
while the other one takes the
pouch inside the stall with him.

32:05.971 --> 32:07.804
That's the weak point.

32:16.648 --> 32:18.881
Elizabeth: Come on.
Where are you taking me?

32:20.685 --> 32:22.818
I don't like surprises,
Philip.

32:24.889 --> 32:26.855
It won't be long.

32:48.612 --> 32:50.545
[ Engine shuts off ]

33:17.373 --> 33:19.440
[ Sighs ]

33:25.681 --> 33:28.115
Do you remember
when they gave us this?

33:30.919 --> 33:32.953
General Zhukov:
This is everything.

33:32.988 --> 33:36.356
Birth certificates,

33:36.391 --> 33:40.060
Social Security cards,

33:40.095 --> 33:42.162
driver's licenses.

33:45.901 --> 33:48.235
Marriage license.

33:53.541 --> 33:56.242
You want
to make it official?

34:09.924 --> 34:12.158
[ Stairs creaking ]

34:13.795 --> 34:17.797
So... keep in mind,
I didn't have many options.

34:17.831 --> 34:20.431
Gabriel ran this guy
for years.

34:20.467 --> 34:22.668
And he's from home.

34:40.187 --> 34:43.521
This is Father Andrei.

34:43.556 --> 34:46.757
You look different.
No mustache.

34:46.793 --> 34:49.060
I don't have to worry
about anyone seeing us.

34:51.496 --> 34:53.563
You will be married.

34:53.599 --> 34:56.034
As for the State,
whoever comes to Moscow first

34:56.069 --> 34:59.203
